messages.message:
:star: Thank you all for the burst of feedback over the past 24 hours (May 16-17) in the feedback document, this will really help us improve the AIHub offering :grinning:

To help us keep up with feedback better moving forward, letâ€™s follow the below process to track and understand your feedback.

1. *Please add your feedback as a new Slack message in <#C0516UPPMT3|> instead of adding them to the feedback document.*
2. On a daily basis, AIHub EMs and PMs will respond to your Slack message in thread if we need more details. 
3. Once we have the necessary details, we will create Jira tickets for each issue to track fixes and share the ticket in your thread.
4. Once we have reviewed the thread, we will emoji react to the Slack message to confirm that it is tracked.
5. If you do not get engagement on feedback that you file in Slack, please ping @Eric Han @Hari @Varun Jain and @avi on your thread.
You will can lookup issues we are tracking in Jira in this query (https://instabase.atlassian.net/issues/?jql=status+in+%28Backlog%2C+%22In+Progress%22%2C+%22In+Review%22%2C+New%2C+%22To+Do%22%29+AND+labels+%3D+aihub-feedback+ORDER+BY+priority+DESC&atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNzc0NjViZGVjM2VkNGMwNDlkNTBlMWI1YzA3MmM1ZDMiLCJwIjoiaiJ9). Please do not directly add issues to this query, we will add them on your behalf.
